title: Dharma
subTitle: Intolerant of injustice, Dharma is arrested for killing a man for molesting his sister. Upon his release, he becomes a powerful gangster to fight off evil in society.

title: Aanazhagan
subTitle: Raja disguises himself as a married woman to find a rental house for his friends. However, trouble brews when he falls for the landlady's daughter.
During a curfew imposed in two quarreling villages, a small-time thief, a driver and an artist team up to steal gold from an unjust politician.

title: Otran
subTitle: A group of terrorists kidnaps Sudha and takes over her apartment to save their employer Robert. Karthik, a RAW agent, pretends to be a cook and goes to her house to capture the entire gang.

title: Thayumanavan
subTitle: A police officer invites three prisoners to his house for Diwali. As they celebrate, the prisoners tell him why they hate women.

title: Sami Potta Mudichu
subTitle: Kadhirvelan wishes to take revenge on his uncle, who is responsible for his grandfather's death. However, he changes his mind after he meets Neelaveni, his uncle's daughter.

title: Vedham Pudhithu
subTitle: Vaidehi belongs to an orthodox Brahmin family and falls in love with Sankarapandi who is from a different caste. Their love is disapproved by her father but is accepted by Sankarapandi's family.

title: Makkal Aatchi
subTitle: Sethupathi, a common man, gets lucky when he accidentally finds a large amount of money in a truck. He decides to use the money to enter politics and ends up becoming the chief minister of the state.
